Paper: hep-th/9412014

Date: 1994-12-02

Title: Entropy of Extremal Black Holes in Two Dimensions

Authors: Alok Kumar and Koushik Ray

Comments: 11 pages

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D51 (1995) 5954-5957

Entropy for two dimensional extremal black holes is computed explicitly in afinite-space formulation of the black hole thermodynamics and is shown to bezero {\it locally}. Our results are in conformity with the recent one byHawking et al in four dimensions.